Maybe ok for a speed clash. The IP address is irrelevant and it seems most of the problem is about realizing how trivial it is; e.g., a 2-line python program:

for i in xrange(int(raw_input())):
    print (1 << (32- int(raw_input().split('/')[1]))) - 2

Works for me in shortest :

main(n){
    char s[9];
    for(gets(s),
          *s-48?:puts("ERROR");
           gets(s);
           printf("%i\n",(int)(n?(32-log2(2+n)):exp2(32-atoi(s+1))-2)))
                !(n=atoi(s))?:putchar(47);
}

Nice clash!
